---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`About ${site.name}`}>
  <div class="static-page site-container article-body">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      {site.name} is a text-first publication on frontier AI, research analysis, and deep technology. It publishes briefs, research notes, long essays, and field maps — structured so you can read one piece or follow a topic for months.
    </p>

    <h2>Who it is for</h2>
    <p>
      Engineers, researchers, policy readers, and technically curious people who want primary-source context and clear argument — not press-release summaries or product marketing dressed as analysis.
    </p>

    <h2>What it covers</h2>
    <p>
      AGI directions, world models, evaluation, compute, interpretability, safety, open-source systems, data-efficient learning, and regional context (including India & AI). Coverage follows what is actually moving in research — not whatever is trending on social feeds.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Clarity over hype.</li>
      <li>Sources over vibes.</li>
      <li>Accessible, not shallow.</li>
      <li>Opinion is labeled as opinion.</li>
      <li>Corrections are welcome.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>About the author</h2>
    <p>
      Written and edited by a single author. Replace this paragraph with your background — institution, focus areas, and why you publish — in plain language.
    </p>

    <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Email: <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .static-page {
    padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .static-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .static-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
